Vernam cipher
*************

A C++ program demonstrating the implementation of Vernam cipher.



To run the program
******************

1. Go the directory where the file is present.

2. To build the program, type make in the terminal.

3. The program has now been built and the executable file a.out is ready.

4. To run the executable file, type ./a.out in the terminal.
   
5. The plaintext has been encrypted. The decryption process retrieves the plaintext from the ciphertext. 
   The results at each stage of the encryption and decryption process are also displayed.

6. To remove the unnecessary files, type make clean into the terminal
   The executable file a.out and the object files will be removed



